# ✨ 1st time use: update the "Load model" nodes! ✨

## These are the nodes in the Backend area of the workflow you need to check
> (make sure all the Workflows are turned on in the first switch)

### In "Model Loader" group

1) Load Diffusion Model (flux1-dev.safetensors)
2) Dual Clip Loader (t5xxl_fp16.safetensors and clip_l.safetensors)
3) Load VAE (ae.safetensors)


### In "2.FLUX Inpaint workflow" and "3.FLUX Outpaint workflow" groups

1) Load Diffusion Model (flux1-fill-dev.safetensor)


### In "4.FLUX Kontext workflow" and "5.FLUX Kontext Multi-Image wf" groups

1) Load Diffusion Model (flux1-kontext-dev.safetensor)


### In "6.FLUX Tools - Canny" group

1) Load Diffusion Model (flux1-canny-dev.safetensor)

### In "7.FLUX Tools - Depth" group

1) Load Style Model (flux1-depth-dev.safetensor)
2) DownloadAndLoadDepthAnythingV2Model (depth_anything_v2_vitl_fp32.safetensors)


### In "FLUX Redux workflow" group

1) Load Diffusion Model (flux1-redux-dev.safetensor)
2) Load CLIP Vision (sigclip_vision_patch14_384.safetensors)

## These are the nodes in the Frontend area of the workflow you need to check

### In "Upscale settings" group

1) Load Upscale Model (4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensor or any other of your choice)
2) Load Skin-Detail Upscale Model (x1-ITF-SkinDiffDetail-Lite-v1.pth)

nodes.title: INSTRUCTIONS
widgets_values:
# FLUX Modular WF - How to use
### Flux base model (with text encoders and Vae)

Based on the [ComfyUI's example page on Github](https://comfyanonymous.github.io/ComfyUI_examples/flux/) and [ComfyUI Official Documentation](https://docs.comfy.org/)

1) [Flux.1 Dev](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-dev/blob/main/flux1-dev.safetensors) - save in ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/ folder
2) [t5xxl_fp16.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/t5xxl_fp16.safetensors) - save in ComfyUI/models/text_encoders/ folder
3) [clip_l.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/clip_l.safetensors) - save in ComfyUI/models/text_encoders/ folder
4) [ae.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Lumina_Image_2.0_Repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/vae/ae.safetensors) -  save in ComfyUI/models/vae/ folder
### Flux extras (Kontext, Fill, Redux, Canny and Depth)
1) [Flux.1 Kontext](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Kontext-dev)  - save in ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/ folder
2) [Flux.1 Fill](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Fill-dev)  - save in ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/ folder
3) [Flux.1 Redux](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Redux-dev) - save in ComfyUI/models/style_models folder
4) [sigclip_vision_patch14_384.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/sigclip_vision_384/blob/main/sigclip_vision_patch14_384.safetensors) - save in ComfyUI/models/clip_vision folder
5) [flux1-canny-dev.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Canny-dev) - save in ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/ folder
6) [flux1-depth-dev.safetensors](https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.1-Depth-dev) - save in ComfyUI/models/diffusion_models/ folder

You will also need a couple of upscale models:
1) [Skin Detail upscale model](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/x1_ITF_SkinDiffDetail_Lite_v1.pth?download=true) for skin-detail enhancement (in Upscaler module)
2) An Upscale model of your choice (suggested: [4x-UltraSharpV2](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensors?download=true) )

LUT files must be saved inside the Custom Node folder: "/ComfyUI/custom_nodes/comfyui_layerstyle/lut/".  You can find a few LUT files I use [here](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/tree/main/luts). 

The Workflow uses 14 Custom nodes you will need to download and install (use ComfyUI Manager!): Impact Pack, Custom Scripts, Rgthree nodes, Easy Use, KJNodes, Crystools, UltimateSDUpscale, Comfyroll Studio, Detail Daemon, DepthAnythingV2, Impact-subpack, Image Saver, Image metadata extension, ComfyUI LayerStyle.

Load an image (you can [download the standard example image from here](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/example.png?download=true)) in each one of the three "Load images" in the top right corner of the WF.

⚠️*Hint: using keys "1", "2" and "3" will let you navigate in the workflow, from the Frontend area of the wf to the Backend area and then to the Instructions area.*⚠️

Update all the "Load model" nodes (most of them are in the Backend of the wf, just activate all the modules and press "2"). ***See the Red Notes node below.***

---

## Select the workflow and the modules

Go to the Switches group (*press "1"*) and select between the seven different workflows available. Please, choose only one!

Next, you should select what modules you want to use.  I suggest to start generating only with the basic workflow, without any module active.  Once you find a good prompt and the right settings, you can start develop your image by using HiRes Fix, the Upscaler and the other modules.  PostProduction module is always active, but you can use the default settings if you don't want to apply any Postproduction to the image.  Last, you can chose if you want to save the image with all the metadata (for example if you want to upload the image on CivitAI), and also you can choose if you want to save each single output from each module of the workflow too.

In the Image Comparer settings choose which images you want to compare in the large Preview node in the middle of the workflow.  

⚠️*Hint:  if you keep the seeds fixed, you can change the preview quickly, without the need to re-generate the images*⚠️

---


### 🎨 Inpaint/Outpaint (⚠️***set Flux Guidance to 30.0***⚠️)
The Inpaint workflow uses the Flux 1 Fill model.  You may have to test a few different seeds and settings to get a valid output. 
You need to load an image and draw a mask on it, where you want to apply Inpaint: **right click on the loaded image, select "Open in Mask editor" and draw the mask**. 

⚠️Inpaint will not work with HiRes-Fix module⚠️, since the Inpaint latent image is very peculiar (it only affects part of the image, the one you masked) it can not work with the HiRes-Fix module.

 ---

### ♻️ Redux
Redux is some sort of IP-Adapter that will allow you to transfer a style from the image you upload (you can use up to three images in a Redux workflow).  With the release of Flux Kontext, Redux is now less interesting. 

---

### 🖌️ Canny/Depth (⚠️***set Flux Guidance to 30.0 for Canny and to 10.0 for Depth***⚠️)
Flux's Controlnets are limited to Canny and Depth, but you can achieve a lot with just these two tools.  You don't need Openpose for example, as you could use Canny or Depth to get similar results.  
These are very powerful tools for Flux image generation.

---


### 🪄 Kontext
FLUX.1 Kontext is a breakthrough multimodal image **editing model** that supports simultaneous text and image input, intelligently understanding image context and performing precise editing. Its development version is an open-source diffusion transformer model with 12 billion parameters, featuring excellent context understanding and character consistency maintenance, ensuring that key elements such as character features and composition layout remain stable even after multiple iterative edits.
There are two different Kontext workflow:
1) Standard Editing wf - just upload one or more images and merge them the way you like (merge styles, merge subjects, etc.);
2) Multi-image wf - from the image you upload, this wf will output 4 different images based on the uploaded one.  Just write the 4 different prompts to be applied to the uploaded image and you will get 4 consistent output.  Extremely useful when you want to keep consistency with, for example, a character portrayed in the loaded image.

---

## 🖋️ Prompt and settings 🧩
Now it's time to input your prompt (Flux uses only positive prompt), and to set up the workflow's settings. The size of the image you want to generate, the number of steps, the Flux Guidance (stay around 3.00-3.50 unless you are using Inpaint/Outpaint or Canny/Depth), the sampler and scheduler, the seed (random or fixed), the batch size, the denoise (use 1.00 for txt2img generation, around 0.40-0.60 for img2img generation).  You can use the DetailDaemon node (set detail_amount to 0.00 to turn it off, suggested value is 0.10).  Then you can select LoRAs' and their strength (you can get info about each lora you use from CivitAI too: right-click on the Lora and select "Show Info").  You can also set the Inpaint blur settings if you are using Inpaint workflow.

---

## 😎 Generate your image 😎
Just press "Run" and wait to see your output image.  

---

## Modules available

### HiRes-Fix
Just a small "upscaler" that apply a little upscale to the latent adding also some new details.  Use a small upscale ratio (I suggest between 1.2x - 1.5x, but you can go up to 2.0x).  Denoise and number of steps may have to be fine-tuned according to the images you are working on.

### FaceDetailer
If your image show human faces, this module will try to improve the details and the quality of that part of the image.  There is no standard settings for this module.  You should test different steps, cfg and denoise.  Try also to change Cycle from default 1 to 2 or higher (but it will take longer to complete the generation).

### Ultimate SD Upscaler
In this module you can also use a "Skin-enhancer" model if your image is a realistic portrait.  The skin appearance and details will improve a lot.  You can download here the [1x-ITF-SkinDiffDetail](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/x1_ITF_SkinDiffDetail_Lite_v1.pth?download=true) model.  Save it in the /models/upscale_models/ folder.  I suggest to use the new [4xUltrasharp_v2](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensors?download=true) upscale model as a all-around upscaler.

### Overlay Settings
This is only for testing purposes.  This module will write all the settings used in the generation over the image itself, so you can have a quick reference about what you used to generate that image.

### Save Image with Metadata
This module will save the final image (only) with all the metadata about the prompts and settings used in the generation.  This is very useful if you want to keep all these info on your outputs or if you want to upload the image on websites like CivitAI.


---

For any other information you can contact me on my [Patreon page](https://www.patreon.com/c/Tenofas), where all my Workflows will always be free for all!  Or on my [CivitAI page](https://civitai.com/user/Tenofas).
